<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Known from sandy bottoms, but also a scavenger by implication (
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry, JK" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 148" refId="B129" refString="Lowry, JK, Stoddart, HE, 1997. Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae. Memoirs of the Hourglass Cruises 10: 1 - 148" title="Amphipoda Crustacea IV. Families Aristiidae, Cyphocarididae, Endevouridae, Lysianassidae, Scopelocheiridae, Uristidae." volume="10" year="1997">Lowry and Stoddart 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
This species was described from three specimens: two from fish stomachs in the Gulf of Mexico and in the collections of the USNM, and another specimen taken in a trawl off Argentina by the USS 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Albatross</emphasis>
in the collections of the AM. No new material has been recorded in the literature since its description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
